<br>
Mages don't get any sort rune spell, meaning your life taps are your friend.<br>
<br>
Dispell his pet and let it duke it out with yours.  If the mage nukes your pet down, just root it.<br>
<br>
Drop a Vexing Mordiana on the mage, even if he dispells it will keep your hps up if he tries to nuke you down.<br>
<br>
Then drop a Insdisious Retrogression, it might get resisted if it does, move on.  If not, the mage is basically dead if you follow up next step.<br>
<br>
Chain cast Deflux.  Its great and with Vex keeping your hps up, you should be able to drop the mage.<br>
<br>
P.S. Its very important to dispell mage pet.  Pet is usually buffed with haste, expediance.  Don't try to root the pet first, as a good mage will have buffed his pet such that he'll leave room for dot slots and then just dispell your snare/root w/o dispelling pet haste.<br>
<br>
Devourium Spiritmonger<br>
57 level Heretic, Rallos Zek<br>
